The corridor had now stretched on well over one hundred feet. Cody glanced to the rear, but saw only Lulu, who had managed to get the leash tangled in one of her front legs and was now trotting on the other three. With a sigh, Cody stopped and laid the leash on the ground, letting Lulu use the slack to disentangle herself. “Constant barking and whining, and the only time you don't make any noise is when there is actually a problem. You really shouldn't be taking your cues from my marriage.”
